## One-time steps (not committable — must be run by hand)
{% if native_marketplace and 'claude' in agentic_targets and agentic_plugins | length > 0 %}
### Claude: activate external plugins

Run once per workspace to register the marketplace plugins:

```sh
{% for plugin in agentic_plugins -%}
claude plugin install {{ plugin.name }}@{{ plugin.owner_repo }} --scope project
{% endfor -%}
```

These commands persist to the Claude workspace state (outside git) and cannot be represented as committed files.
{% endif %}
{% if 'kiro' in agentic_targets and mcp_config %}
### Kiro: enable MCP in the IDE

Open the Kiro IDE → Settings → MCP → toggle **Enable MCP servers** ON. This is a one-time IDE toggle; the MCP server configuration is committed in `.kiro/settings/mcp.json`.
{% endif %}
